    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="203"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d203fn1">Channel of transmission not indicated.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d203fn2">The message originated at Quebec
                            but was apparently transmitted via London.</note>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-11">11 August
                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President. Personal and
                    most secret. Number 409.<note n="3" xml:id="d203fn3">For the passages not
                        printed here, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_578">p.
                            578</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>It is quite cool here and very pleasant and everything is ready for you in
                    Citadel which is admirably suited to our needs. It was indeed a happy
                    inspiration which led you to suggest this particular rendezvous at this
                    particular moment in Canadian politics.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
